OL,3,C80% of 85 to 95-year-olds now pay with
OL,4,Ccontactless, says Barclays
OL,6,FMore than a fifth (22%) of people aged
OL,7,F18 to 34 regularly leave their wallet
OL,8,Fbehind when out shopping in favour of
OL,9,Fpaying with their smartphone, compared
OL,10,Fwith just 1% of over-75s.
OL,12,FKaren Johnson, head of retail at
OL,13,FBarclays, said: "In 2024, we expect to
OL,14,Fsee a greater shift to payments using
OL,15,Fmobile wallets, as more bricks-and-
OL,16,Fmortar businesses integrate the
OL,17,Ftechnology into their customer
OL,18,Fexperience.
